Arsenal have set their sights on signing Sheffield United duo John Fleck and George Baldock ahead of the summer window. An Arsenal source has told us that manager Arteta has been hugely impressed by the duo&rsquo;s performances, including in the 1-1 draw on Saturday. [<br />
@SportsPeteO<br />
]<br />
<br />
Fleck has a contract that expires in the summer of 2021, which makes the Blades vulnerable to interested clubs at the end of this campaign. Meanwhile, Balcock's contract expires in 2022.'

